 --001a11c1e8b8811b6304ebf8a222
 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
 
 Looking at the code a bit, I see that what DrRacket currently does is
 call string-normalize-nfkc which already turns non-breaking space into
 ordinary space, but doesn't turn the non-breaking minus sign into an
 ordinary hyphen.
 
 It also adds a special case for \u200b, tho, I see. So I'll just add
 another one for \u2212 and optimistically close the PR.
 
 If that seems insufficient, feel free to re-open (or just reply, of course).
 
 Robby
 
 --001a11c1e8b8811b6304ebf8a222
 Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8
 Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
 
